frameDefinitions: A Material is used to make a Product.
A piece of Evidence indicates that an Event occured, or metonymically, Entity had formerly existed, in a Location.
An Agent manipulates a Fastener to open or close a Containing_object (e.g. coat, jar).
This frame contains nouns denoting Quantities of a specified Entity and their numerical Values.
In this frame an Emission emanates from a Source along a Path or to a Goal.
In this frame a Fluid moves from a Source to a Goal along a Path or within an Area.  '
frameExamples: These cooking <t><fex name='mat'>ingredients</fex></t> are readily available.
He was careful to make sure that there was no <t>trace</t> of tampering in the file.
Mary <t>closed</t> her coat with a belt.
His heart attack was caused by a high cholesterol <t>level</t>.
listRoleDefinitions: The entity which is used to make a <fen>Product</fen>.
The purpose for which the <fen>Material</fen> is intended.
The entity or substance that is created out of the <fen>Material</fen>.

The thing that indicates an Entity was in a Location.

He found traces of the burglar in the hallway.

The thing whose former existence in a Location can be deduced from the <fen>Evidence</fen>.

Traces of the former inhabitants can still be found in the abandoned manor.
An event whose details are revealed through the discovery of <fen>Evidence</fen>.
A description of the time that an <fen>Event</fen> occurs or an <fen>Entity</fen> exists at a place.

This role identifies the item that is closed by the agent with the fastener.
<fex name='Agent'>Lee</fex> <t>buttoned</t> <fex name='Containing_object'>his coat</fex>.
The Agent opens/closes the Containing-object.
This role identifies the fastener that the agent manipulates.
This role identifies the active zone of the container that may be expressed as the direct object of the target verb.
The time at which the <fen>Agent</fen> closes the <fen>Container_portal</fen> or the <fen>Containing_object</fen>.
The location where the closing event takes place.
<fen>Entity</fen> identifies the concept or substance being quantified by a <fen>Quantity</fen>.
Identifies the <fen>Quantity</fen>-denoting <t>target</t> word.
<fen>Value</fen> identifies the numerical amount of the <fen>Entity</fen>.
The <fen>Emission</fen>s are discharged out of the <fen>Source</fen> .
The <fen>Source</fen> is the location from which the <fen>Emission</fen> emanates.
This role identifies the time when the emanation occurs.
<fen>Area</fen> is the setting in which the <fen>Fluid</fen>'s movement takes place on an unspecified <fen>Path</fen>.
<fen>Goal</fen> is the location the <fen>Fluid</fen> ends up.
The <fen>Path</fen> is the trajectory along which the <fen>Fluid</fen> moves.
The <fen>Source</fen> is the location the <fen>Fluid</fen> occupies initially.
The <fen>Fluid</fen> is the entity that changes location and moves in a fluidic way.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Fluid</fen> flows.
The Place describes the location of the motion which has a specified Source, Path or Goal.
listRoleExamples: Add all the <fex>ingredients</fex>, toss and chill.
Supply and placing of <fex>building</fex> materials shall be incidental to installation of the paving stones.
Marcus tied his shoe <fex>with the neon-green shoelaces</fex>.
They close the bank vault <fex>at precisely 5:35PM</fex>.
Shouldn't you have buttoned that <fex>in the bathroom</fex>?
Their <fex><t>level</t></fex> of productivity decreased with each hour of overtime worked.
He wrote me a check in the amount <fex>of $500</fex>.
<fex>At Oregon Caves</fex>, a stream runs through the dining room.
